html
    head
        meta(charset="UTF-8")
        title File Metadata Microservice API
        link(rel="stylesheet"
             href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.0.0-alpha.6/css/bootstrap.min.css"
             integrity="sha384-rwoIResjU2yc3z8GV/NPeZWAv56rSmLldC3R/AZzGRnGxQQKnKkoFVhFQhNUwEyJ"
             crossorigin="anonymous")
    body
        div(class="jumbotron"
            style="margin: 5%")
            h2 File Metadata Microservice API
            p:a dmiten |
                a(href="https://github.com/dmiten/FCC-backend-FileMetadata"
                  target="blank")  GitHub
            <br><br>
            <b><i>User Stories:</i></b>
            li I can submit a FormData object that includes a file upload.
            li When I submit something, I will receive the file size in bytes within the JSON-response.
            <br>
            <b><i>So</i></b>, use next form to submit a file and receive JSON-answer.
            <br><br><br>
            div(class="alert alert-info")
                form(action="/upload"
                     enctype="multipart/form-data"
                     id="fileUpload"
                     method="post"
                     name="fileUpload")
                    input(name="userFile"
                          type="file")
                button(form="fileUpload"
                       onclick="handleSubmit()"
                       type="button") Submit
            div(class="alert alert-success") Last uploaded:
                <br><br>
                span(id="response") none
        script(src="./script.js")